        <abstract>
            <p>Charles Martins has given the first Darwinian lectures on zoology at Montpellier.</p>
            <p>Joseph Duval-Jouve is also a Darwinian. The latter has lost his position as Inspector of the Academy because of his liberal views.</p>
            <p>Wallace suggests that a trap-door spider with an exposed nest preys on nocturnal insects.</p>
        </abstract>
